      <section eId="sec_47_17_103">
        <num>47-17-103</num>
        <content>
          <p>The right to any pension, annuity, allowance, or benefit; to the return of contributions; to a pension, annuity, allowance or benefit itself; to any optional benefit, or any other right accrued or accruing to any person under this chapter; and to moneys under this chapter shall be exempt from any tax imposed by this state, county, municipal, or other political subdivision, except as provided in Code Section 48-7-27; exempt from levy and sale, garnishment, attachment, or any other process whatsoever; and shall be unassignable unless otherwise specifically provided for in this chapter.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1962, p. 39, ยง 9; Ga. L. 1982, p. 3, ยง 47; Ga. L. 2000, p. 1449, ยง 10.)</p>
